quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  54,9,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them; they rejected Our slave and said, “He is a madman,” and he was rebuked"
  54,10,"So he called upon his Lord, “I am overpowered, so help me!”"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of the sky with water pouring down in torrents
  54,12,"and We caused the earth to burst forth with springs, then the waters met for a preordained purpose"
  54,13,"We carried him on an [Ark made] of planks and nails"
  54,14,"sailing under Our [watchful] Eyes; as a reward for the one [they] denied"
  54,15,We have certainly left it as a sign; is there anyone to take heed
  54,16,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,17,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,18,‘Ād disbelieved. Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,19,We sent against them a furious wind on a day of continuous misfortune
  54,20,"sweeping people away, as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees"
  54,21,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,22,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,23,Thamūd rejected the warnings
  54,24,"They said, “Shall we follow a single human being from among us? Then we would surely be in error and insanity"
  54,25,"Has the revelation been sent down upon him out of all of us? Rather, he is an insolent liar.”"
  54,26,Tomorrow they will know who the insolent liar is
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a test for them, so watch them [O Sālih] and be patient"
  54,28,and tell them that the water is to be shared between them; each should take its drink in turn
  54,29,"But they called their companion, and he undertook the task and hamstrung her"
  54,30,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent against them a single blast, leaving them like trampled hedge-building twigs"
  54,32,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,33,The people of Lot rejected the warnings
  54,34,"We sent against them a storm of pebbles, except the family of Lot whom We saved before dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishing assault, but they doubted the warnings"
  54,37,"They even demanded that he let them have their way with his angel-guests, so We blinded their eyes, [saying], “Taste My punishment and My warnings!”"
  54,38,By the early morning a lasting torment overtook them
  54,39,Taste My punishment and My warnings
  54,40,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,41,"Indeed, warnings came to the people of Pharaoh"
  54,42,"But they rejected all of Our signs, so We seized them with the grip of the All-Mighty, Most Powerful"
  54,43,"Are your disbelievers [O Makkans] superior than those, or have you been granted immunity in divine Scriptures"
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We are a united front, bound to prevail.”"
  54,45,"Soon their united front will be defeated, and they will flee"
  54,46,"But the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour is more catastrophic and more bitter"
  54,47,"Indeed, the wicked are in error and will be in blazes"
  54,48,"On the Day when they will be dragged into the Fire on their faces, [they will be told], “Taste the agony of Hell!”"
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created everything according to a determined measure"
  54,50,"Our command is but a single word, which is fulfilled in the blink of an eye"
  54,51,"We have destroyed many like you [O Makkans]; is there anyone to take heed"
  54,52,Everything they did is in the written records
  54,53,"and everything, small or big, is written down"
  54,54,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and rivers"
  54,55,seated in honor in the presence of the Most Powerful Sovereign